The paper focuses on solving the problem of high-resolution image blending using a combination of classical gradient-based approaches and Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of GANs indicates that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves image processing and manipulation, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
